	 (193,2,NULL,187,8,NULL,'<p>I think there isn''t a single meaning, and sometimes it might be a simple <em>brofist</em>, showing respect to one another. But there''s also to consider that Bee, in a way, uses fist bumps to read the other person''s mind/heart/soul, to feel the other person; he does it with the Raikage.</p>

<p>But for example</p>

