	 (43,29,1,'You might want to clarify on what you mean by "more efficient".  Shorter time to make, cost-benefit ratio?','2012-12-11 21:36:31',NULL,22,'CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (44,42,6,'That''s the problem I have.  I mean everyone seems to "know" this...I did as well.  And yet, when I asked someone Japanese about it (far more likely to know about the cultural norms than me), they had no idea what I was talking about (and were very adamant that it was *not* the case that it was sexual.)','2012-12-11 21:37:38',NULL,36,'CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (45,15,1,'@MozenRath: No, I didn''t explicitly say that. That''s why I said, that''s how I understood it, and it also makes the most sense. That''s why my soul started leaving my body, and then it returned, because I reinitiated the technique.','2012-12-11 21:38:07',NULL,27,'CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (49,45,0,'Since you mention the fanart aspect, I think your answer is more complete.','2012-12-11 21:42:59',NULL,38,'CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (51,20,4,'It depends on which ending you go with.  I believe the anime she lived, whereas in the manga, it is at least stated that she died.','2012-12-11 21:44:59',NULL,26,'CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (55,50,6,'This sounds like guesswork to me.  (I don''t mean that as an insult: it sounds like really *good* guesswork...it makes a lot of sense.)  I''m just also hoping to find some external source to provide some solid evidence about this in one direction.','2012-12-11 21:56:05',NULL,36,'CC BY-SA 3.0');
INSERT INTO comments (Id,PostId,Score,`Text`,CreationDate,UserDisplayName,UserId,ContentLicense) VALUES
	 (56,57,0,'Well, that was why I made the question...it makes a lot of sense.  On the other hand, it was just an educated guess on my part.','2012-12-11 21:57:46',NULL,36,'CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (57,26,0,'As stated, this question is not answerable. Specifically which scenarios (or episodes) are you talking about? If the question were limited only to Athrun''s self-destructing suit, perhaps there''s an answer to be had there.','2012-12-11 21:59:28',NULL,71,'CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (59,57,5,'It''s like asking "Do magazines tend to lose money?", "Do internet startups tend to lose money?", or "Do restaurants tend to lose money?" -- honestly, *anything* that you have to put a big pile of money behind to get started tends to lose money. Anime is not immune just because it''s anime.','2012-12-11 22:01:40',NULL,41,'CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (62,39,5,'(And lemme tell ya...it''s hard finding information on the internet about this...there''s tons of info out there...but it''s pretty much all based on anime/manga, and the conclusion seems to be inferred from guesswork based on the generalized experience.)','2012-12-11 22:03:35',NULL,36,'CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (65,57,1,'Sure, most new business ventures tend to lose money, but we''re comparing apples and oranges to some extent here...  In particular, restaurants are primarily attempting to make a profit.  But I''m wondering more if anime is considered a "loss leader" in general, not expected to really turn a profit.  Secondarily, I''m also wondering if there is a generalized cultural (or other) reason that a profitable show might end.  Here, popular shows tend to continue.  It does not seem like it''s always the case in Japan, which implies that even popular shows may still not be turning a profit.','2012-12-11 22:10:48',NULL,36,'CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (70,65,1,'Not really, unless by "death" you mean "death by Death Note", they are not vulnerable to "death". We''ve seen lifespans ending with unnatural deaths too (like shooting in an ally). So if your lifespan gets extended, you won''t meet that fate so soon.','2012-12-11 22:24:27',NULL,27,'CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (71,65,0,'Yes I meant unnatural deaths','2012-12-11 22:30:29',NULL,28,'CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (73,63,1,'I think its a valid question, but it needs editing to make it more user friendly','2012-12-11 22:40:02',NULL,28,'CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (74,63,0,'What do you mean? Spoiler tags? Or is it something else?','2012-12-11 22:41:05',NULL,49,'CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (75,66,0,'Aya Hirano really is a good example, considering popular shows such as Suzumiya Haruhi and Lucky Star. It may be relevant to note the fan reaction to cases like hers, where she mostly abandons her career (I''m not comenting on that topic since I''m really not sure, but it seems to be that her career as a seiyuu is over).','2012-12-11 22:43:05',NULL,38,'CC BY-SA 3.0');
