	 (135,2,57,'7939281a-c2ec-4673-8368-ae32486a0186','2012-12-11 21:56:48',41,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You have to remember that **it''s far cheaper and easier to produce a manga** than it is to produce an anime -- it takes fewer people to produce a manga, which means less money is needed to pay for production, even if you pay everyone involved a huge salary (and you usually don''t).

More investment means more risk, so if an anime doesn''t turn a big enough profit fast enough, it may not warrant further investment. 

You can keep a crap manga going a lot longer than a crap anime, if only because the bar for financial security is that much lower.','CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (136,2,58,'3d3fb5e7-e01c-471e-9a0e-ea04d176599e','2012-12-11 21:57:13',49,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'**Regarding Fullmetal Alchemist:** I suppose that what you consider a reboot is actually Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood. If that is so, the answer is **YES**. The reason being that it is not +actually+ a reboot in the real sense of it: it is actually the *real* story, in the way that it actually follows the Manga much more faithfully than the first series.

**Regarding Neon Genesis Evangelion:** I don''t really know, since I''ve only seen the original series.

**However:** I don''t see this as an ''either...or...'' choice. There are *reboots* that are really good and original series that are nothing special, but there are also bad *reboots* and very good original new series. It depends on you being more interested in watching something *really* new for you, or reviewing something ''old'' that you really enjoyed!','CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (137,2,59,'ed71ba9d-80b1-407a-af55-a53a0718349c','2012-12-11 21:59:03',15,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'I''m sorry I don''t know Neon Genesis Evangelion, so I''ll answer the FMA part.

Two animes were done: *Full Metal Alchemist* and *Full Metal Alchemist: Brotherhood*.

While they both start the same way, the first one starts to develop in a whole different way than the Manga. This is because when it was being aired, the Manga was not done yet. So they invented.

The second was done after the Manga ended so it respects the original Manga much more. I watched both because I didn''t know of this distinction. Even if the first one is not so faithful, it was of very good quality, so you can give it a try.','CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (138,2,60,'bbd6acee-f19b-4b24-b3bb-35ff33fc20ac','2012-12-11 22:00:24',31,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'I think that this question don''t have a general answer.

