	 (160,5,58,'c7b65d86-9355-48ec-bf08-1a1a2ebc4793','2012-12-11 22:21:17',49,NULL,'modified according to the new question',NULL,NULL,'Brotherhood is actually more faithful to the Manga. The first *''version''* follows the Manga to some extent (about half the show) although it adds some details that do not follow the Manga. The *''reboot''* actually catches up to the first version rather fast (in about the first 4th) and then has *''new material''* (comparing to the first one) until the end of it. Brotherhood also has more episodes (64, compared to 51) ','CC BY-SA 3.0'),
	 (161,5,58,'c9b721d9-1c4f-42d5-9e74-b12603a1cebd','2012-12-11 22:27:22',49,NULL,'added more details',NULL,NULL,'Brotherhood is actually more faithful to the Manga. The first *''version''* follows the Manga to some extent (about half the show) although it adds some details that do not follow the Manga.
