	 (199,2,81,'55344e04-e237-4b3c-aca5-37ca45410634','2012-12-11 23:00:38',63,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'No matter how you look at it an anime is a cartoon. The main difference is that an anime is a Japanese style cartoons. 

Domestic cartoons and anime can vary in drawing styles, based on the staff, budget, and character/set designs. Anime series are typically more detailed than your average domestic show as there is more of a abundance of technically skilled artists than there are domestically.

Both can reach different age regardless of their initial target audience (E.g., Avatar: The Last Airbender, My Little Pony and Adventure Time for an example). Typically domestic cartoons are more light hearted when compared to Japanese anime. Both can deal with more mature themes, in both a serious (like Cyber 6) and humorous light (As with Futurama, South Park, Simpsons, and Family Guy). There are domestic cartoons for adults just like there are 18+ anime in Japan.

If you ask the average person in your country and one in Japan both will consider them to be childish. The difference between anime and cartoons is very subjective. It typically comes down to what you like and how you like it.


','CC BY-SA 3.0'),
